{"id": 7127, "title": "Ticket #7127: Parsing of octal and hexidecimal literals broken in ClassAds", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen an integer literal in octal format (i.e. leading '0') is encountered when parsing a <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span> expression, the lexer always returns an error. When an integer literal in hexadecimal format (i.e. leading '0x') is encountered, lexer returns an integer literal of '0' when in old <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span> or JSON parsing mode.\n\n<p>We can fix the lexer to properly handle octal integers when in new <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAds\" title=\"Class Ads\">ClassAds</a></span> format and reject octal and hex integers when in old or JSON format.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2019-Aug-01 17:13:30 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE_REVIEW</strong> looks good.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Aug-05 16:53</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1541c6bde0a87ba52a39df04d867ce3a45b5a8ea\">[57598]</a></span>: Docs for octal/hex integer fix in <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAds\" title=\"Class Ads\">ClassAds</a></span>. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7127\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7127'); return false;\" title=\"Parsing of octal and hexidecimal literals broken in ClassAds\">#7127</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Jul-09 16:36</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1f480a8bfb47c721139ae1c0f4b4e678ced8a853\">[57359]</a></span>: Fix parsing of octal and hex literals in <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAds\" title=\"Class Ads\">ClassAds</a></span>. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7127\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7127'); return false;\" title=\"Parsing of octal and hexidecimal literals broken in ClassAds\">#7127</a></span> Reject octal and hexidecimal formats when in old <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span> or JSON mode. Properly read octal format when in new <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAd\" title=\"Class Ad\">ClassAd</a></span> mode.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2019-Aug-05 16:54", "status": "resolved", "created": "2019-Jun-24 13:37", "fixed_version": "2019-Jun-24 13:37", "broken_version": "", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "ClassAd", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}